296
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:29,772
All the films planned up until that point got shelved.

297
00:22:29,797 --> 00:22:33,414
In reaction, I wrote "Nikudan."

298
00:22:34,093 --> 00:22:40,293
There was no green light on the project, but I still wanted to write it.

299
00:22:41,120  -->  00:22:46,564
The battle between the director and the studio is in many ways just as hard as the filmmaking, eh?

301
00:22:46,565 --> 00:22:48,252
Yeah.

302
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:53,000
I think that's happening everywhere, unless you pay for it all yourself.

304
00:22:57,000  -->  00:23:00,700
